62. To further extend the capacity of the banking system to play a key role in a rapidly growing economy, the Bank of Ghana has increased the capital requirements of banks. The Bank of Ghana has set the new minimum capital requirement at $\mathrm{GH}
ot\propto
ot60$ million to be met by end of 2009. Banks with majority domestic shareholders however, are required to increase their minimum capital to $\mathrm{GH}
ot\propto25$ million by end 2010, and then to $\mathrm{GH}
ot\propto60$ million by end 2012.
